Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using Transformer networks to translate natural language math word problems to equivalent arithmetic expressions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning to solve math word problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper explores different neural network configurations and their performance. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential category as the paper uses neural networks to solve math word problems. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of neural networks to recognize and translate visual representations of math word problems.
